            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-669] introduce HttpRoutePlanner interface</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-669</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>Define an interface to determine a route for a given target host.&lt;br/&gt;
Create default implementation replacing DefaultHttpClient.determineRoute(...);&lt;br/&gt;
Implementations will need access to params and/or request.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The interface fits into HttpConn, but DHC.dR(...) uses client parameters.&lt;br/&gt;
Either move parameters to HttpConn, or keep default implementation in HttpClient.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Alternative implementations could evaluate Java system properties related to proxy settings.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
